The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, January 29, 2004 				 Baijal leads home race
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Jan. 28: Anil Baijal, a 1969 batch IAS officer from the Union Territory cadre, will be the new Union home secretary. The announcement is expected later tonight.																								The current incumbent, . Gopalaswami, has been shifted to the Election Commission after T.S. Krishnamurthy, one of the two election commissioners, was elevated to the post of the chief election commissioner.																								Krishnamurthy replaces J.M. Lyngdoh, who is scheduled to retire on February 7.																								Fertiliser secretary Nripendra Mishra and Rajeev Ratan Shah, secretary, communications and information technology, both 1967 batch officers, are also in the race. 																								So is M. Shankar, secretary, rural development, a 1967 batch Haryana cadre.																								Baijal is currently vice-chairman of the Delhi Development Authority and is reputed to be a brilliant officer. 																								He has served a term as additional secretary in the information and broadcasting ministry and was the CEO of Prasar Bharati.
